HEADWORD: Dedicator
<hw>Ded"i*ca`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧dicateur</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who dedicates; more
especially, one who inscribes a book to the favor of a patron, or to one
whom he desires to compliment.</def>⟦br⟧
